                    <span class="opener__topics ">
            <a class="opener__topics-link " href="https://www.propublica.org/topics/racial-justice">Racial Justice</a>
        </span>
    
    <h1 class="opener__hed " >        The University Uprooted a Black Neighborhood. Then Its Policies Reduced the Black Presence on Campus.
    </h1>

    <h2 class="opener__dek " >        Black enrollment at Virginia’s Christopher Newport University fell by more than half under longtime president Paul Trible, a former Republican senator who wanted to “offer a private school experience.” By 2021, only 2.4% of full-time professors were Black.
    </h2>

    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

</div>
        
<div class="article-meta-1
     article-meta-1--left     " data-pp-location="article meta">

    <span class="article-meta-1__byline" data-pp-location="article byine">
        by <span class="name">Brandi Kellam</span> and <span class="name">Louis Hansen</span>, <a href="https://vcij.org/">Virginia Center for Investigative Journalism at WHRO</a>, and <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/gabriel-sandoval">Gabriel Sandoval</a>, ProPublica    </span>
    <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
        <time class="timestamp" datetime="2023-12-22EST06:00">Dec. 22, 2023, 6 a.m. EST</time>
    </time>

